[{"id":"VR188308","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of two charged particles located along a horizontal axis that is labeled x, in centimeters. There are five equally spaced tick marks along the axis labeled 0 through 4, in increments of 1. One particle, which has a charge of positive Q, is located at the tick mark for 0 centimeters. The other particle, which has a charge of negative Q, is located at the tick mark for 4 centimeters.\" height=\"54\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR188308.g04.png\" width=\"300\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two charged particles are located on the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>-axis, as shown in the figure above. One particle with a charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is located at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 0 centimeters\"><math alttext=\"x equals 0 centimeters\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mtext></mtext><mtext> cm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and the other particle with a charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative Q\"><math alttext=\"negative Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>−</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is located at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 4 centimeters\"><math alttext=\"x equals 4 centimeters\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mtext> cm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Where can a third particle of charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 4 Q\"><math alttext=\"positive 4 Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> be located so that the net force on the particle at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 4 centimeters\"><math alttext=\"x equals 4 centimeters\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mtext> cm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is zero?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR188308_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 2 centimeters\"><math alttext=\"x equals 2 centimeters\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext> cm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 8 centimeters\"><math alttext=\"x equals 8 centimeters\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mtext> cm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 12 centimeters\"><math alttext=\"x equals 12 centimeters\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn><mtext> cm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 20 centimeters\"><math alttext=\"x equals 20 centimeters\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mtext> </mtext><mtext>cm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]